    "We first apply our FCC-ee likelihood to derive bounds on the selected operators discussed in section 4.",
    "These constraints are obtained after applying the ε i factors (see figure 6), i.e.",
    "in the scenario with NP around the TeV scale coupled dominantly to the third generation.The results are shown in figure 8.",
    "This analysis reveals that FCC-ee holds the potential to significantly improve the bounds on a large fraction of the representative set of effective operators.",
    "The strongest increase in sensitivity occurs for purely third-family four-fermion operators, such as C(3)[3333] ℓq and C (3)[3333] qq, whose current bounds are suppressed only by ε F. These operators are strongly constrained by FCC-ee due to their y t -enhanced running into Z-pole observables."
